data.name: lblOverviewDetails.Text
data.value: You can control how much detail you wish to deal with. You may start by specifying a few fields to import in order to get a quick look at how the FieldWorks Data Notebook works, and then come back later and specify more and more fields. This Import Procedure is designed to allow you to refine the process iteratively until you are finally satisfied with the result.

data.name: lblOverviewSafety.Text
data.value: Note, FieldWorks will not make any changes to the standard format files you are importing.

data.name: lblBackupInstructions.Text
data.value: Back up the FieldWorks project before importing. Then, if you are not satisified with the results of the import, you can restore the backup to undo the import.

data.name: lblOverviewInstructions.Text
data.value: This procedure will guide you through the process of importing Standard Format data into the Notebook of the current FieldWorks Project.

data.name: lblProjectFileInstructions.Text
data.value: If you have the project file for this Shoebox/Toolbox database, specify it here. (Import can continue without the project file, but you will need to supply more information.)

data.name: lblSaveAsInstructions.Text
data.value: Your import settings will be saved to this file, for use in any future imports.

data.name: lblSettingsInstructions.Text
data.value: Select an import settings file. You will be able to modify/customize these settings to fit the database you're importing.

data.name: lblDatabaseInstructions.Text
data.value: Specify the standard format file containing the anthropology data you want to import.

data.name: lblMappingLanguagesInstructions.Text
data.value: Verify the encoding converters used for the writing systems in {0}.

data.name: lblContentInstructions1.Text
data.value: For each marker in your standard format file, indicate its destination in the current FieldWorks Notebook by selecting a row and then clicking on the Modify button. (You will want to verify any educated guesses that FieldWorks may have made.)

data.name: lblHierarchyInstructions.Text
data.value: Records in the FieldWorks Notebook support hierarchical embedding of records. If your standard format file contains hierarchy, you need to map it onto the FieldWorks Notebook's structure. For example, mapping "\lnf" onto "Event (level 2)" indicates that the import process should start a new sub-record whenever it encounters a \lnf field. (Refer to Help for more details.)

data.name: labelStep5Description.Text
data.value: A Record Marker is used in a Standard Format file to mark the beginning of each record. FieldWorks has attempted to determine the Record Marker for this database. If this is not the correct marker, please select it here.

data.name: lblCharMappingInstructions.Text
data.value: Indicate any markup you have used in your data to identify character styles, writing systems, or direct formatting.

data.name: lblReadyToImportInstructions.Text
data.value:
You are now ready to import your anthropology data into FieldWorks.
To begin importing, click Finish.

data.name: m_rbAddEntries.Text
data.value: Add (the Notebook area will contain both old Records and newly imported data.)

data.name: m_rbReplaceAllEntries.Text
data.value: Overwrite all existing Records in the Notebook area. (Use this option to redo an import.)

data.name: lblAddOrReplaceInstructions.Text
data.value: Your final decision is whether or not to replace any existing contents of the {0} notebook.
